ost academically outstanding cadets  VMI recruits  develops  and graduates cadets of exceptional talent  intellectual curiosity  and character  who possess a commitment to service and respect for others  Dedicated Faculty98 percent of faculty hold Ph D s and are renowned for teaching excellence  mentorship  scholarly engagement  commitment to service  and encouragement of undergraduate research  Cadet study areas are adjacent to faculty offices  encouraging individual instruction and in depth communication  Academic SupportAcademic support services are designed to help cadets achieve their academic and professional goals  Services such as the Miller Academic Center  the Office for Academic Athletic Advising  the Math Education and Resource Center  and Career Services work together to help each cadet reach his or her full potential  More about Support   Small ClassesSmall class sizes allow faculty to interact closely with cadets inside and outside the classroom  Typically our teacher to student ratio is about 11 1  Distinguished VisitorsWell known dignitaries  experts  and leaders regularly come to VMI to address the Corps of Cadets  offering diverse and stimulating perspectives on a wide range of topics  Center for Leadership and EthicsVMI s Center for Leadership and Ethics enhances the cadet experience by offering a range of opportunities for academic and character development  Cadets participating in the center s programs discuss leadership challenges  meet authors  and interact with distinguished leaders  Go to Center for Leadership and Ethics   Focus on LearningMany cadets point to the absence of ordinary college distractions and the presence of personal accountability as guideposts for their success  Academic Prizes  Medals  and Awards Academics Majors   Minors Areas of Study Course Catalog Enrichment Programs Services   Support Summer Programs Research at VMI Scholarships Office of the Dean Dean s Office P   540  464 7212 F   540  464 7719 Dean s Office Virgin